      "content": "I'm trying to compile a dossier on the legal status of the Republic of Altynia. It was a sovereign state in the Central Asian steppe that was effectively scrubbed from official UN records and most maps after the 1954 border shifts. I have several family documents claiming a continuous line of succession from the Altyni dynasty, but I need to find any surviving international legal precedents or treaty fragments that might recognize their prior sovereignty. Can you help me look into the historical legitimacy of the Altynian throne?",
